article.headline: Pennsylvania 68, Dartmouth 52
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Zoller had 17 points and 11 rebounds and Ibrahim Jaaber broke his own school and league records for steals in a season as Penn defeated Dartmouth 68-52 Saturday night. Jaaber, the nation's leader in steals per game with 3.2, had four steals Saturday and has 87 this season, breaking last season's record of 85. Eric Osmundson had 14 points and Steve Danley and Brian Grandieri 10 each for the Quakers (18-7, 10-1 Ivy), who defeated Dartmouth for the 19th straight time. Dan Biber had 14 points and Mike Lang 11 for the Big Green (5-20, 3-9), who made only 22 of 58 shots in the game. Penn jumped out to a 19-5 lead and held a 30-23 edge at halftime. Dartmouth rallied to within 32-29 on a four-point play by Lang with 17:25 remaining, but Penn went on a 13-4 run to stretch the lead to 45-33 and was never threatened again.
